-- Greece Should Exit Euro Unless It Reforms, Dobrindt Tells Bild
-- B y   R a i n e r   B u e r g i n
-- 2012-02-12T14:51:30Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-12/greece-should-exit-euro-unless-it-reforms-dobrindt-tells-bild.html
Greece  should exit the euro region
voluntarily if its government fails to implement the policy
changes it promised in return for financial aid, Alexander Dobrindt, general-secretary of  Germany ’s Christian Social Union,
told  Bild am Sonntag .  Officials should try to convince the Greek government that
an orderly exit from the euro is better than the threat of an
“uncontrolled collapse,” Dobrindt told the newspaper.  To contact the reporter on this story:
